  "prompt": "Is it OK to cook vegetables (gravy) and dal for a whole week on Sunday and then put them in the fridge and eat one every day?",
  "response": "While it's convenient to meal prep, there are some important considerations:\n\n1. Food Safety:\n- Cooked food should be refrigerated within 2 hours of cooking\n- Store in shallow containers to cool quickly\n- Consume within 3-4 days for optimal safety and quality\n\n2. For Dal and Gravy:\n- Dal can last 3-4 days in the refrigerator\n- Gravy might last 2-3 days, depending on ingredients\n- After that, quality and taste may deteriorate\n- Risk of bacterial growth increases\n\n3. Recommendations:\n- Cook for 3-4 days ahead, not a full week\n- Reheat thoroughly (at least 165\u00b0F/74\u00b0C)\n- Store in airtight containers\n- Keep refrigerated at or below 40\u00b0F/4\u00b0C\n- If possible, prepare fresh or in smaller batches\n\n4. Best Practices:\n- Freeze portions if you want to keep food longer\n- Thaw and reheat properly\n- Check for any signs of spoilage before eating\n\nFor the best taste, nutrition, and safety, it's advised to cook for 3-4 days maximum, not a full week.",
